"title": "7525: exclusiveness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7525: exclusiveness",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The keeping of a distinctive group identity by drawing clear boundary lines, to separate those within the group from outsiders with whom they are unwilling to associate.</p>\n<h2>The practice of exclusiveness by God's people, grounded in God's claim to exclusive worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:3\">EXO 20:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:7\">DEU 5:7</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:14\">EXO 34:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:14-Deut6:15\">DEU 6:14–6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:35-2Kgs17:39\">2KI 17:35–17:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:8\">ISA 42:8</a></p>\n<h2>Exclusiveness in Israel, a practical expression of being a people set apart</h2>\n<h3>An expression of being set apart for God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:26\">LEV 20:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:31\">LEV 15:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:23-Lev20:24\">LEV 20:23–20:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:1-Deut7:6\">DEU 7:1–7:6</a></p>\n<h3>An expression of being set apart from others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num23:9\">NUM 23:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:7\">JOS 23:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:21\">EZR 6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:1-Neh13:3\">NEH 13:1–13:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:9\">EZK 44:9</a></p>\n<h2>The practice of exclusiveness</h2>\n<h3>Expressed in the avoidance of marrying outsiders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:30\">NEH 10:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:3-Deut7:4\">DEU 7:3–7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:1-Ezra9:4\">EZR 9:1–9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:9-Ezra10:17\">EZR 10:9–10:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:23-Neh13:27\">NEH 13:23–13:27</a></p>\n<h3>Expressed in a refusal to eat with outsiders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:10-Matt9:11\">MAT 9:10–9:11</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:15-Mark2:16\">MRK 2:15–2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:29-Luke5:30\">LUK 5:29–5:30</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:1-Luke15:2\">LUK 15:1–15:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:12\">GAL 2:12</a></p>\n<h2>The marks of Jewish exclusiveness</h2>\n<h3>Circumcision</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:9-Gen17:14\">GEN 17:9–17:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:48\">EXO 12:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:3\">LEV 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:8\">ACT 7:8</a></p>\n<h3>Festival observance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:14-Exod12:16\">EXO 12:14–12:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:17-Exod12:20\">EXO 12:17–12:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:26-Lev23:29\">LEV 23:26–23:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:13\">NUM 9:13</a></p>\n<h3>Observance of food laws</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:17\">LEV 3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:22-Lev7:27\">LEV 7:22–7:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:1-Lev11:47\">LEV 11:1–11:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:10-Lev17:14\">LEV 17:10–17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:29\">ACT 15:29</a> <em>While food restrictions were not a requirement of the gospel, Gentile believers are here asked to respect the scruples of Jewish Christians in those areas that were traditionally important to them.</em></p>\n<h3>Sexual relations restricted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:6\">LEV 18:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:7-Lev18:30\">LEV 18:7–18:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:10-Lev20:21\">LEV 20:10–20:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:20-Deut27:23\">DEU 27:20–27:23</a></p>\n<h2>Effects of Jewish exclusiveness</h2>\n<h3>Division between Jews and Samaritans</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:9\">JHN 4:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:1-Ezra4:3\">EZR 4:1–4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:5-Matt10:6\">MAT 10:5–10:6</a> <em>Jesus Christ was here dealing with his priority for that time</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:51-Luke9:53\">LUK 9:51–9:53</a></p>\n<h3>Division between Jews and Gentiles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:28\">ACT 10:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:5\">MAT 10:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:21-Matt15:28\">MAT 15:21–15:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:24-Mark7:30\">MRK 7:24–7:30</a> <em>Jesus Christ restricted his earthly ministry in general to the people of Israel, but instigated a mission to the Gentiles after his resurrection</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:28\">JHN 18:28</a></p>\n<h2>The problem of Jewish exclusiveness among the first Christians</h2>\n<h3>The negative evaluation of Gentiles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:1-Acts11:18\">ACT 11:1–11:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:11-Gal2:13\">GAL 2:11–2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:15\">GAL 2:15</a></p>\n<h3>The requirement that Gentile believers be circumcised</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:1\">ACT 15:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:5\">ACT 15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:2-Gal5:6\">GAL 5:2–5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:12\">GAL 6:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:10\">TIT 1:10</a></p>\n<h2>Jewish exclusiveness overturned</h2>\n<h3>By God giving his Spirit to the uncircumcised Gentiles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:8\">ACT 15:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:44-Acts11:18\">ACT 10:44–11:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:13\">1CO 12:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:2-Gal3:5\">GAL 3:2–3:5</a></p>\n<h3>By the argument of justification by faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:15-Gal2:16\">GAL 2:15–2:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:9-Acts15:11\">ACT 15:9–15:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:28-Rom3:30\">ROM 3:28–3:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:9-Rom4:12\">ROM 4:9–4:12</a></p>",
